President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate Brian D. Montgomery of Texas as Deputy Secretary of Housing and Urban Development. Montgomery currently serves as Assistant Secretary for Housing, Federal Housing Commissioner at the Department of Housing and Urban Development (HUD). If confirmed, this will be the second time Montgomery has served as head of the Federal Housing Administration (FHA) and the third administration he has worked under. As Assistant Secretary for Housing, Montgomery oversees HUD's project-based Section 8 rental assistance housing program, the Office of Housing Counseling, and HUD's Manufactured Housing Program. He is also responsible for managing FHA's mortgage insurance portfolio worth over $1.4 trillion. With over 30 years of experience in both the public and private sectors, Montgomery brings extensive knowledge of housing issues and policy initiatives to HUD.

President Trump also intends to nominate Thomas B. Chapman of Maryland as a Member of the National Transportation Safety Board. Chapman currently serves as minority counsel to the Senate Commerce Subcommittee on Aviation and Space. He has almost four decades of experience in government, legislative, and regulatory affairs, with involvement in various issues related to aviation and transportation. Chapman has worked on bipartisan efforts to pass comprehensive legislation reauthorizing the Federal Aviation Administration, Transportation Security Administration, and National Transportation Safety Board. He has previously held positions at US Airways, Southwest Airlines, and the Aircraft Owners and Pilots Association. Chapman is a graduate of the American University Washington College of Law and C.W. Post College.